{
  "text": "Another alternative that has prevailed in the last thirty years consists of several approaches all known under the generic name of continuous or rational thermodynamics, although continuum and rational may not be exactly synonymous. They can be in general classified as entropy theories and entropy free thermodynamics. The latter seem to have serious deficiencies so we shall not worry about them here [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The former ones basically start from the assumption that the so-called Gibbs-Duhem equation holds true in a finite volume of the system, namely",
  "correct_citation": {
